title: 820-00165 No USB activity
message:
Clean perfect board, VCORE 1.8V steady, SMC bypass same thing

Already tried:
Clean known good BIOS
Different SMC
Removed Q8150
Replaced U1950
Heated up PCH with good flux

PP3V3_SUS 3.3V
PLT_RESET_L present 3.3V
PLT_RST_BUF_L 3.3V
ALL_SYS_PWRGD 3.3V
PM_S0_PGOOD 3.4V

title: 820-00165 No USB activity
message:
Possibly bad CPU.

Check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and traces.
Did you remove airport card and SSD?
Test the board alone, no LIO flex, nor trackpad.

Check all resistors from LPC bus.
Is there any activity on the o-scope?

title: 820-00165 No USB activity
message:
All my test are done with bare board and known good LIO flex and board.
Tried no LIO flex, same thing.
Looks like CPU is muerto!
